px\">China blocks Meta-Manus deal</h2></table><table align=left border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 valign=top><tr><td style=\"padding:0 10px\"><span><!--[if mso]><img alt=\"Meta logo. \"src=\"https://img.semafor.com/a9d36f1aafdab678f0566833982a711baa5ca57e-2048x1153.jpg?rect=0,1,2048,1152&w=576&h=324&q=95&auto=format\"width=576 height=324><div> </div><figcaption style=font-family:Courier;font-size:.75rem;font-weight:400;display:block;line-height:120%>Gonzalo Fuentes/File Photo/Reuters</figcaption><div> </div><span><![endif]--></span><span><!--[if !mso]><! --></span><a clicktracking=off href=# style=display:block><img alt=\"Meta logo. \"height=649 src=\"https://img.semafor.com/a9d36f1aafdab678f0566833982a711baa5ca57e-2048x1153.jpg?rect=1,0,2047,1153&w=1152&h=649&q=95&auto=format\"style=display:block;width:100%;height:auto;padding-bottom:10px width=576></a><figcaption style=\"font-family:Courier;font-size:.75rem;font-weight:400;display:block;line-height:120%;padding:0 0 10px\">Gonzalo Fuentes/File Photo/Reuters</figcaption><span><!--<![endif]--></span><p class=dmwt style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;padding:0;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#1f1d1a;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;font-size:1.25rem;line-height:120%;letter-spacing:-.02em\"><strong>Chinese authorities blocked Meta’s purchase of AI startup Manus, deepening a global fissure between Washington and Beijing on leading-edge technologies. </strong>Meta’s Dec. 2025 deal to buy the firm, which specializes in developing AI agents, had been seen as a step towards a global ecosystem for tech startups in which Chinese and American companies might integrate. But Beijing has been <a class=dmlc clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/jToGRsY6Ta?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"style=color:#0e29b5 target=_blank>tightening its oversight of the sector</a>, and even though Manus is headquartered in Singapore, its founders are Chinese and it has significant operations on the mainland. China’s tech industry is increasingly competing with Silicon Valley for global dominance, and Meta’s potential purchase sparked fears of <a class=dmlc clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/vk5C1S0W1o?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"style=color:#0e29b5 target=_blank>a “conspiratorial” effort by the US to keep its rival down</a>.<p class=dmwt style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;padding:0;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#1f1d1a;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;font-size:1.25rem;line-height:120%;letter-spacing:-.02em\"><div data-testid=call-to-action><table align=left border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 style=padding-top:10px;padding-bottom:10px valign=top width=100%><tr><td><span><!--[if !mso]><! --></span><div class=dmyboc style=\"border-top:1px dashed #1f1d1a\"></div><span><!--<![endif]--></span><span><!--[if mso]><table width=100%><tr><td style=\"border-top:dashed 1px #1f1d1a;border-width:1px 0 0 0;height:1px;width:100%;margin:0\"></table><span><![endif]--></span></table><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td valign=top><p class=dmwt style=font-family:Helvetica;font-size:1.125rem;line-height:120%;margin:0>For more on the AI race, <a clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/Gbi3wmdE6S?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"style=color:#243bb5;text-decoration:none>subscribe to Semafor’s Tech briefing</a>. →</table><div style=height:10px></div></div><p></table><div style=text-align:center;width:100%><table style=margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto><tr><td><a aria-label=\"Share with Twitter\"clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/01BTjqOK4b?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"target=_blank><img alt=\"\"src=https://static.semafor.com/_app/static/images/x-post.png width=79></a><td><a aria-label=\"Share with Email\"clicktracking=off href=\"mailto:?subject=%F0%9F%9F%A1+Ceasefires%2C+central+banks%2C+and+conspiracies+%7C+Semafor&body=https%3A%2F%2Fsemafor.com%2Fs%2F5GP749wuQG\"rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"target=_blank><img alt=\"\"src=https://static.semafor.com/_app/static/images/email-link.png width=79></a><td><a aria-label=\"Share with Friends\"clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/5GP749wuQG?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"rel=noreferrer target=_blank><img alt=\"\"src=https://static.semafor.com/_app/static/images/link.png width=100></a></table></div></table></div><div><table align=left border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 valign=top width=100%><tr><td align=center style=\"line-height:25px;padding:20px 0\"><span class=lmda style=\"font-size:30px;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#575757\">↓</span><span><!--[if !mso]><! --></span><span class=dmda style=\"display:none;font-size:30px;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#575757\">↓</span><span><!--<![endif]--></span></table><table class=dmybo id=k style=\"border:1px solid #575757;mso-border-right-alt:1px solid #575757\"width=99%><tr><td style=padding-top:20px;padding-bottom:20px><table id=#k width=100%><tr><td align=center style=padding-bottom:10px><span><!--[if mso]><span class=\"dmyt dmybo\"style=\"font-family:Helvetica;width:fit-content;padding:4px 10px;font-size:1.125rem;line-height:21px;color:#575757;margin:0 8px;word-break:break-word;display:inline-block\">9</span><span><![endif]--></span><span><!--[if !mso]><! --></span><span class=\"dmyt dmybo\"style=\"font-family:Helvetica;width:fit-content;padding:4px 10px;font-size:1.125rem;line-height:21px;color:#575757;margin:0 8px;word-break:break-word;display:inline-block;border:1px solid #575757;border-radius:999px\">9</span><span><!--<![endif]--></span></table><table align=left border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 valign=top width=100%><tr><td align=center style=\"padding:10px 0 19px\"><h2 class=dmyt style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:2rem;line-height:110%;font-weight:400;margin:0 10px\">Latam’s worsening demographics</h2></table><table align=left border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 valign=top><tr><td style=\"padding:0 10px\"><span><!--[if mso]><img alt=\"A chart showing the falling fertility rate in Latin America\"src=\"https://img.semafor.com/3da4e1ca92e851bde990eb13fb6e403d9b48f99d-1066x974.png?rect=0,1,1066,973&w=576&h=526&q=95&auto=format\"width=576 height=526><div> </div><span><![endif]--></span><span><!--[if !mso]><! --></span><a clicktracking=off href=# style=display:block><img alt=\"A chart showing the falling fertility rate in Latin America\"height=1053 src=\"https://img.semafor.com/3da4e1ca92e851bde990eb13fb6e403d9b48f99d-1066x974.png?w=1152&h=1053&q=95&auto=format\"style=display:block;width:100%;height:auto;padding-bottom:10px width=576></a><span><!--<![endif]--></span><p class=dmwt style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;padding:0;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#1f1d1a;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;font-size:1.25rem;line-height:120%;letter-spacing:-.02em\"><strong>Latin America has become the fastest-aging part of the world, raising fears that it will grow old before it can become rich. </strong>For decades, the region had one of the world’s largest demographic bonuses, with births per woman <a class=dmlc clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/HhHrQRoEl2?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"style=color:#0e29b5 target=_blank>peaking at almost six in the 1960s</a>. However population growth has since plummeted to well below replacement levels: Chile, one of Latin America’s wealthiest countries, now has a fertility rate below that of Japan, the global archetype of a demographic crisis. The crisis will shape “politics, businesses, communities, <a class=dmlc clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/n1plNsdBrf?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"style=color:#0e29b5 target=_blank>and how people live for decades to come,</a>” Americas Quarterly said.</table><div style=text-align:center;width:100%><table style=margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto><tr><td><a aria-label=\"Share with Twitter\"clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/xr2XnCWPZh?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"target=_blank><img alt=\"\"src=https://static.semafor.com/_app/static/images/x-post.png width=79></a><td><a aria-label=\"Share with Email\"clicktracking=off href=\"mailto:?subject=%F0%9F%9F%A1+Ceasefires%2C+central+banks%2C+and+conspiracies+%7C+Semafor&body=https%3A%2F%2Fsemafor.com%2Fs%2Fvw8DMXX8KB\"rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"target=_blank><img alt=\"\"src=https://static.semafor.com/_app/static/images/email-link.png width=79></a><td><a aria-label=\"Share with Friends\"clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/vw8DMXX8KB?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"rel=noreferrer target=_blank><img alt=\"\"src=https://static.semafor.com/_app/static/images/link.png width=100></a></table></div></table></div><div><table align=left border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 valign=top width=100%><tr><td align=center style=\"line-height:25px;padding:20px 0\"><span class=lmda style=\"font-size:30px;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#575757\">↓</span><span><!--[if !mso]><! --></span><span class=dmda style=\"display:none;font-size:30px;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#575757\">↓</span><span><!--<![endif]--></span></table><table class=dmybo id=l style=\"border:1px solid #575757;mso-border-right-alt:1px solid #575757\"width=99%><tr><td style=padding-top:20px;padding-bottom:20px><table id=#l width=100%><tr><td align=center style=padding-bottom:10px><span><!--[if mso]><span class=\"dmyt dmybo\"style=\"font-family:Helvetica;width:fit-content;padding:4px 10px;font-size:1.125rem;line-height:21px;color:#575757;margin:0 8px;word-break:break-word;display:inline-block\">10</span><span><![endif]--></span><span><!--[if !mso]><! --></span><span class=\"dmyt dmybo\"style=\"font-family:Helvetica;width:fit-content;padding:4px 10px;font-size:1.125rem;line-height:21px;color:#575757;margin:0 8px;word-break:break-word;display:inline-block;border:1px solid #575757;border-radius:999px\">10</span><span><!--<![endif]--></span></table><table align=left border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 valign=top width=100%><tr><td align=center style=\"padding:10px 0 19px\"><h2 class=dmyt style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:2rem;line-height:110%;font-weight:400;margin:0 10px\">US happiness plummets</h2></table><table align=left border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 valign=top><tr><td style=\"padding:0 10px\"><span><!--[if mso]><img alt=\" People walk by US flags. \"src=\"https://img.semafor.com/587f02e64f77efb0191261f465daf8478593a2dd-2048x1365.jpg?w=576&h=384&q=95&auto=format\"width=576 height=384><div> </div><figcaption style=font-family:Courier;font-size:.75rem;font-weight:400;display:block;line-height:120%>Tyrone Siu/Reuters</figcaption><div> </div><span><![endif]--></span><span><!--[if !mso]><! --></span><a clicktracking=off href=# style=display:block><img alt=\" People walk by US flags. \"height=768 src=\"https://img.semafor.com/587f02e64f77efb0191261f465daf8478593a2dd-2048x1365.jpg?w=1152&h=768&q=95&auto=format\"style=display:block;width:100%;height:auto;padding-bottom:10px width=576></a><figcaption style=\"font-family:Courier;font-size:.75rem;font-weight:400;display:block;line-height:120%;padding:0 0 10px\">Tyrone Siu/Reuters</figcaption><span><!--<![endif]--></span><p class=dmwt style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;padding:0;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#1f1d1a;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;font-size:1.25rem;line-height:120%;letter-spacing:-.02em\"><strong>The US has become startlingly less happy despite being, by most metrics, significantly richer, thanks in large part to interlinked post-pandemic aftershocks, a leading political writer argued.</strong> Americans’ reported well-being was declining steadily for years, but since 2020 has dropped swiftly across all demographics. The suddenness and uniformity imply the usual suspects — smartphones, societal atomization — <a class=dmlc clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/xQfWjRbYx7?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"style=color:#0e29b5 target=_blank>cannot be the whole story</a>, Derek Thompson said. Instead he suggested high inflation has created a “vibecession,” visible in other Western countries, while collapsing trust in institutions and a series of crises filtered through a negative news environment have further eroded public sentiment. The US “was a reasonably happy country for a long time,” Thompson quoted an economist saying. “It is not happy now.”</table><div style=text-align:center;width:100%><table style=margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto><tr><td><a aria-label=\"Share with Twitter\"clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/OV9izWDTgd?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"target=_blank><img alt=\"\"src=https://static.semafor.com/_app/static/images/x-post.png width=79></a><td><a aria-label=\"Share with Email\"clicktracking=off href=\"mailto:?subject=%F0%9F%9F%A1+Ceasefires%2C+central+banks%2C+and+conspiracies+%7C+Semafor&body=https%3A%2F%2Fsemafor.com%2Fs%2FUAgruo4zl3\"rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"target=_blank><img alt=\"\"src=https://static.semafor.com/_app/static/images/email-link.png width=79></a><td><a aria-label=\"Share with Friends\"clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/UAgruo4zl3?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"rel=noreferrer target=_blank><img alt=\"\"src=https://static.semafor.com/_app/static/images/link.png width=100></a></table></div></table></div><div><table align=left border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 valign=top width=100%><tr><td align=center style=\"line-height:25px;padding:20px 0\"><span class=lmda style=\"font-size:30px;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#575757\">↓</span><span><!--[if !mso]><! --></span><span class=dmda style=\"display:none;font-size:30px;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#575757\">↓</span><span><!--<![endif]--></span></table><table class=dmybo id=m style=\"border:1px solid #575757;mso-border-right-alt:1px solid #575757\"width=99%><tr><td style=padding-top:20px;padding-bottom:20px><table id=#m width=100%><tr><td align=center style=padding-bottom:10px><span><!--[if mso]><span class=\"dmyt dmybo\"style=\"font-family:Helvetica;width:fit-content;padding:4px 10px;font-size:1.125rem;line-height:21px;color:#575757;margin:0 8px;word-break:break-word;display:inline-block\">Flagging</span><span><![endif]--></span><span><!--[if !mso]><! --></span><span class=\"dmyt dmybo\"style=\"font-family:Helvetica;width:fit-content;padding:4px 10px;font-size:1.125rem;line-height:21px;color:#575757;margin:0 8px;word-break:break-word;display:inline-block;border:1px solid #575757;border-radius:999px\">Flagging</span><span><!--<![endif]--></span></table><table><body><tr><td style=\"font-size:1.125rem;font-family:Times New Roman;line-height:32px;font-weight:400;color:#1f1d1a;padding:0 10px 20px\"><span><!--[if mso]><img src=\"https://img.semafor.com/c2ab89115ae7225914f4b9840f57724d5a9ad975-1260x413.png?rect=1,0,1259,413&w=570&h=187&q=95&auto=format\"width=570 height=187><div> </div><span><![endif]--></span><span><!--[if !mso]><! --></span><a clicktracking=off href=# style=display:block><img height=374 src=\"https://img.semafor.com/c2ab89115ae7225914f4b9840f57724d5a9ad975-1260x413.png?rect=1,0,1259,413&w=1140&h=374&q=95&auto=format\"style=display:block;width:100%;height:auto;padding-bottom:10px width=570></a><span><!--<![endif]--></span><ul style=clear:both;padding-left:30px><li class=dmwt style=\"margin:0;padding:0;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#1f1d1a;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;font-size:1.25rem;line-height:120%;letter-spacing:-.02em;margin-left:5px;margin-right:10px;margin-bottom:4px;padding-left:0\">Venezuela’s acting president attends an energy industry conference in Caracas, alongside oil executives and other officials.<li class=dmwt style=\"margin:0;padding:0;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#1f1d1a;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;font-size:1.25rem;line-height:120%;letter-spacing:-.02em;margin-left:5px;margin-right:10px;margin-bottom:4px;padding-left:0\">The Stockholm International Peace Research Institute publishes annual military expenditure data.<li class=dmwt style=\"margin:0;padding:0;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#1f1d1a;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;font-size:1.25rem;line-height:120%;letter-spacing:-.02em;margin-left:5px;margin-right:10px;margin-bottom:4px;padding-left:0\">George Clooney receives the Chaplin Award in New York.</ul></tr></body></table><div style=text-align:center;width:100%><table style=margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto><tr><td><a aria-label=\"Share with Twitter\"clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/dAAIiYbdKt?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"target=_blank><img alt=\"\"src=https://static.semafor.com/_app/static/images/x-post.png width=79></a><td><a aria-label=\"Share with Email\"clicktracking=off href=\"mailto:?subject=%F0%9F%9F%A1+Ceasefires%2C+central+banks%2C+and+conspiracies+%7C+Semafor&body=https%3A%2F%2Fsemafor.com%2Fs%2FDakwoFIQI1\"rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"target=_blank><img alt=\"\"src=https://static.semafor.com/_app/static/images/email-link.png width=79></a><td><a aria-label=\"Share with Friends\"clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/DakwoFIQI1?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"rel=noreferrer target=_blank><img alt=\"\"src=https://static.semafor.com/_app/static/images/link.png width=100></a></table></div></table></div><div><table align=left border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 valign=top width=100%><tr><td align=center style=\"line-height:25px;padding:20px 0\"><span class=lmda style=\"font-size:30px;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#575757\">↓</span><span><!--[if !mso]><! --></span><span class=dmda style=\"display:none;font-size:30px;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#575757\">↓</span><span><!--<![endif]--></span></table><table class=dmybo id=n style=\"border:1px solid #575757;mso-border-right-alt:1px solid #575757\"width=99%><tr><td style=padding-top:20px;padding-bottom:20px><table id=#n width=100%><tr><td align=center style=padding-bottom:10px><span><!--[if mso]><span class=\"dmyt dmybo\"style=\"font-family:Helvetica;width:fit-content;padding:4px 10px;font-size:1.125rem;line-height:21px;color:#575757;margin:0 8px;word-break:break-word;display:inline-block\">LRS</span><span><![endif]--></span><span><!--[if !mso]><! --></span><span class=\"dmyt dmybo\"style=\"font-family:Helvetica;width:fit-content;padding:4px 10px;font-size:1.125rem;line-height:21px;color:#575757;margin:0 8px;word-break:break-word;display:inline-block;border:1px solid #575757;border-radius:999px\">LRS</span><span><!--<![endif]--></span></table><table><body><tr><td style=\"font-size:1.125rem;font-family:Times New Roman;line-height:32px;font-weight:400;color:#1f1d1a;padding:0 10px 20px\"><span><!--[if mso]><img alt=\"The London Review of Substacks\"src=\"https://img.semafor.com/257f107f16caf77ecfc16caa1585fefe44ae3807-1917x772.jpg?rect=3,0,1913,772&w=570&h=230&q=95&auto=format\"width=570 height=230><div> </div><span><![endif]--></span><span><!--[if !mso]><! --></span><a clicktracking=off href=# style=display:block><img alt=\"The London Review of Substacks\"height=459 src=\"https://img.semafor.com/257f107f16caf77ecfc16caa1585fefe44ae3807-1917x772.jpg?w=1140&h=459&q=95&auto=format\"style=display:block;width:100%;height:auto;padding-bottom:10px width=570></a><span><!--<![endif]--></span><p class=dmwt style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;padding:0;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#1f1d1a;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;font-size:1.25rem;line-height:120%;letter-spacing:-.02em\"><strong>Victory conditions</strong><p class=dmwt style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;padding:0;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#1f1d1a;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;font-size:1.25rem;line-height:120%;letter-spacing:-.02em\">Early last year, things looked bad for Ukraine: Newly elected President Donald Trump had cut off US aid; Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orbán was doing his best to block EU funds; Russia poured in manpower, hoping to make victory look inevitable and get Trump to pressure Kyiv into surrendering. Crucially, also, Ukraine was all but incapable of striking more than a few miles into Russia: HIMARS rocket artillery had lost effectiveness because of jamming and a shortage of ammunition, while Russia could attack Ukraine’s back line with relative impunity. Now, though, the defense analyst Brynn Tannehill writes in The Bulwark, <a class=dmlc clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/GIfFw49Ix8?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"style=color:#0e29b5 target=_blank>things look very different</a>.<p class=dmwt style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;padding:0;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#1f1d1a;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;font-size:1.25rem;line-height:120%;letter-spacing:-.02em\">Ukraine has an advantage over Russia in both number and quality of drones, and can hit high-value targets such as anti-aircraft radar at medium range or infrastructure such as oil refineries at longer range, up to 600 miles. Meanwhile, Russia has suffered extraordinarily high casualties, the country faces a labor shortage, and army recruiters are accepting “alcoholics, drug addicts, amputees, [and] felons.” The Russian spring offensive stalled immediately; at the rate it took territory in March, it would take 1,775 years to conquer Ukraine. “Things aren’t great for Ukraine either,” says Tannehill. The country’s electrical system is battered and its own recruiting situation is dire. But “for the first time in years, outright victory seems possible.”<p class=dmwt style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;padding:0;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#1f1d1a;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;font-size:1.25rem;line-height:120%;letter-spacing:-.02em\"><strong>…And Justice for All</strong><p class=dmwt style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;padding:0;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#1f1d1a;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;font-size:1.25rem;line-height:120%;letter-spacing:-.02em\">Modern political philosophy is dominated by one man: John Rawls. Of the field’s five most-cited 20th-century works, two are by Rawls, and three are responses to him. “Every decade or so a new book comes along, promising to shift the paradigm,” says the political philosopher Joseph Heath in Persuasion. “Each one has fizzled out, sending us all back to Rawls.” Before Rawls, philosophers largely tried to answer first-order questions about what it meant to create a good society. Rawls, instead, treated it as a political problem: Given that we have many groups who disagree about what a just world looks like, what principles do we need to protect our abilities to pursue those ideals?<p class=dmwt style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;padding:0;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#1f1d1a;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;font-size:1.25rem;line-height:120%;letter-spacing:-.02em\">Some modern conservative thinkers have proposed a post-liberal vision, but, says Heath, they are in an important sense pre-Rawls; they make no effort to think politically about justice. They “are still playing the old game, seemingly oblivious to how Rawls changed the terms of the discussion.” Rawls would have responded, Heath says, along the lines of: Well done, <a class=dmlc clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/guqvxMFcEB?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"style=color:#0e29b5 target=_blank>you’ve expressed your own conception of the good life</a>; now you just need to convince everyone else to follow it. Until you manage it, we still need principles to govern our institutions, and Rawlsian liberalism is still the best we have.<p class=dmwt style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;padding:0;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#1f1d1a;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;font-size:1.25rem;line-height:120%;letter-spacing:-.02em\"><strong>Don’t put metal in the science oven, Rosalyn</strong><p class=dmwt style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;padding:0;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#1f1d1a;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;font-size:1.25rem;line-height:120%;letter-spacing:-.02em\">A few years ago, Marie T. Smith’s 1985 recipe book <em>Microwave Cooking for One</em> gained the attention of the internet, heralded as “the world’s saddest cookbook.” To modern readers, microwave cooking is largely associated with students or divorced men eating lonely ready meals. But “this is completely misinterpreting <em>Microwave Cooking for One</em>’s vision,” writes the pseudonymous blogger Malmesbury on Telescopic Turnip. In 1985, the microwave was on the upward trajectory of its adoption curve; it was new and exciting. Smith, the author, was “a microwave maximalist” — she had stopped owning a stove, and expected microwaves to replace them entirely.<p class=dmwt style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;padding:0;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#1f1d1a;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;font-size:1.25rem;line-height:120%;letter-spacing:-.02em\">She used it to cook steak and pasta. She developed techniques to engender the Maillard reaction — the not-quite-burning browning effect that makes traditional cooking tasty. She used specialized equipment to make crispy veggies or poached eggs (Malmesbury exploded the latter). Any food you can make, Smith made in a microwave. Microwaves became low-status once widely adopted, the “curse that threatens every new easy-to-use technology,” Malmesbury says. But in some other timeline of history, “<a class=dmlc clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/0jnNZpb9Ez?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"style=color:#0e29b5 target=_blank>Marie T. Smith won and Big Teflon lost</a>,” and the microwave took over the kitchen.<p class=dmwt style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;padding:0;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#1f1d1a;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;font-size:1.25rem;line-height:120%;letter-spacing:-.02em\"><em>— Tom Chivers</em></tr></body></table><div style=text-align:center;width:100%><table style=margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto><tr><td><a aria-label=\"Share with Twitter\"clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/SfmPha7pan?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"target=_blank><img alt=\"\"src=https://static.semafor.com/_app/static/images/x-post.png width=79></a><td><a aria-label=\"Share with Email\"clicktracking=off href=\"mailto:?subject=%F0%9F%9F%A1+Ceasefires%2C+central+banks%2C+and+conspiracies+%7C+Semafor&body=https%3A%2F%2Fsemafor.com%2Fs%2FCgoPhKb9hy\"rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"target=_blank><img alt=\"\"src=https://static.semafor.com/_app/static/images/email-link.png width=79></a><td><a aria-label=\"Share with Friends\"clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/CgoPhKb9hy?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"rel=noreferrer target=_blank><img alt=\"\"src=https://static.semafor.com/_app/static/images/link.png width=100></a></table></div></table></div><div><table align=left border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 valign=top width=100%><tr><td align=center style=\"line-height:25px;padding:20px 0\"><span class=lmda style=\"font-size:30px;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#575757\">↓</span><span><!--[if !mso]><! --></span><span class=dmda style=\"display:none;font-size:30px;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#575757\">↓</span><span><!--<![endif]--></span></table><table class=dmybo id=o style=\"border:1px solid #575757;mso-border-right-alt:1px solid #575757\"width=99%><tr><td style=padding-top:20px;padding-bottom:20px><table id=#o width=100%><tr><td align=center style=padding-bottom:10px><span><!--[if mso]><span class=\"dmyt dmybo\"style=\"font-family:Helvetica;width:fit-content;padding:4px 10px;font-size:1.125rem;line-height:21px;color:#575757;margin:0 8px;word-break:break-word;display:inline-block\">Semafor Recommends</span><span><![endif]--></span><span><!--[if !mso]><! --></span><span class=\"dmyt dmybo\"style=\"font-family:Helvetica;width:fit-content;padding:4px 10px;font-size:1.125rem;line-height:21px;color:#575757;margin:0 8px;word-break:break-word;display:inline-block;border:1px solid #575757;border-radius:999px\">Semafor Recommends</span><span><!--<![endif]--></span></table><table><body><tr><td style=\"font-size:1.125rem;font-family:Times New Roman;line-height:32px;font-weight:400;color:#1f1d1a;padding:0 10px 20px\"><span><!--[if mso]><img src=\"https://img.semafor.com/8e2cf2b9cba51014e070f0c14612fc175180d6eb-2048x1537.jpg?rect=1,0,2047,1537&w=570&h=428&q=95&auto=format\"width=570 height=428><div> </div><span><![endif]--></span><span><!--[if !mso]><! --></span><a clicktracking=off href=# style=display:block><img height=856 src=\"https://img.semafor.com/8e2cf2b9cba51014e070f0c14612fc175180d6eb-2048x1537.jpg?rect=1,0,2047,1537&w=1140&h=856&q=95&auto=format\"style=display:block;width:100%;height:auto;padding-bottom:10px width=570></a><span><!--<![endif]--></span><p class=dmwt style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;padding:0;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#1f1d1a;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;font-size:1.25rem;line-height:120%;letter-spacing:-.02em\"><strong><em>Sisters in Yellow</em> by Mieko Kawakami, translated by Laurel Taylor and Hitomi Yoshio.</strong> Kawakami is best known in the West for her novel <em>Breasts and Eggs</em>. This serialized novel about women scrabbling to survive in the underbelly of 1990s Tokyo was serialized in Japan in 2023 but this is its first English translation; The New Yorker named it <a class=dmlc clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/9B8COQ3FcM?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"style=color:#0e29b5 target=_blank>one of its books of 2026 so far</a>, while The Times of London said it proved Kawakami to be “<a class=dmlc clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/dEuj8GKoSl?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"style=color:#0e29b5 target=_blank>the most exciting Japanese novelist at work today</a>.” <a class=dmlc clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/l1dfcDwVI4?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"style=color:#0e29b5 target=_blank>Buy <em>Sisters in Yellow</em> from your local bookstore</a>.</tr></body></table><div style=text-align:center;width:100%><table style=margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto><tr><td><a aria-label=\"Share with Twitter\"clicktracking=off href=\"https://semafor.com/s/uHXZhuTxlg?email=wschenk@gmail.com\"rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"target=_blank><img alt=\"\"src=https://static.semafor.com/_app/static/images/x-post.png width=79></a><td><a aria-label=\"Share with Email\"clicktracking=off href=\"mailto:?subject=%F0%9F%9F%A1+Ceasefires%2C+central+banks%2C+and+conspiracies+%7C+Semafor&bo